The paper discusses a Byzantine Fault Tolerant replicated datastore, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The paper also mentions scalability and latency, which are common concerns in database systems (cs.DB). The use of conditional endorsements and application-level voting also suggests a focus on security and trust in the system, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR) and systems and control (cs.SY).
